  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is advice to a man at age 33 who failed at business and earning money, and who still lives with family?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're going through a challenging time. Many successful individuals have experienced setbacks before achieving their goals. Here are some pieces of advice that may be helpful:\n\n1. **Reflect and Learn**: Take some time to analyze what went wrong with your business and your approach to earning money. Understanding your mistakes can prevent you from repeating them and can guide you in making better decisions in the future.\n\n2. **Consider New Opportunities**: The business world is vast and constantly evolving. Stay open to exploring different industries, markets, or even entirely new career paths. Sometimes a fresh perspective can lead to unexpected opportunities.\n\n3. **Build Skills**: Invest in yourself by enhancing your skills and knowledge. Consider taking courses, attending workshops, or seeking mentorship in areas that interest you or align with your career aspirations.\n\n4. **Set Clear Goals**: Define what success looks like for you and set realistic, achievable goals. Break them down into smaller steps to make the journey manageable and to foster a sense of accomplishment.\n\n5. **Network and Connect**: Building and nurturing professional relationships can open doors to new opportunities. Attend industry events, join relevant online communities, and actively seek advice and support from others in your field.\n\n6. **Financial Management**: Work on improving your financial literacy. Create a budget, save strategically, and consider seeking advice from a financial advisor to help you manage your money more effectively.\n\n7. **Mental and Emotional Health**: Remember that setbacks can take a toll on your mental and emotional well-being. Don't hesitate to seek support from a therapist or counselor to navigate these feelings and develop resilience.\n\n8. **Support System**: Lean on your family and close friends for support. Having a solid foundation of people who believe in you can make a significant difference, both emotionally and practically.\n\n9. **Patience and Persistence**: Success often requires patience and determination. Stay committed to your goals and keep pushing forward, even when the road ahead seems uncertain.\n\n10. **Mindset and Attitude**: Maintain a positive attitude and cultivate a mindset geared towards growth. Believe in your ability to overcome setbacks and adapt to new circumstances.\n\nRemember that many successful individuals have faced failures before achieving their goals. Your current situation doesn't define your future potential. Keep striving, and don't let setbacks deter you from your path to success.",
